The paper is about General Question Answering (QA) systems over texts, which falls under the category of Natural Language Processing (NLP) and Computational Linguistics (CL). The paper specifically investigates the multi-hop reasoning capability of various existing models proposed for multi-hop QA tasks, which is a common topic in the sub-category of CL (cs.CL). The paper also involves the use of machine learning models, which is a common topic in the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG). The paper also involves information retrieval and text analysis, which are common topics in the sub-category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Computer Vision (cs.CV).
